===Etymology===
From {{inh-lite|zh|sit-pro|*g-(j/r)a||right (hand)}} (STEDT). Cognate with {{cog-lite|bo|sc=Tibt|གཡས||tr=g.yas|right}}, {{cog-lite|kac|hkra||tr=khʒa⁵⁵|right}}, {{cog-lite|my|sc=Mymr|ယာ|tr=ya}}, {{m-lite|my|sc=Mymr|ညာ|tr=nya}}.

{{och-l|友|be friendly; friend}} is the endoactive derivation of {{och-l|右|id=1}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

{{och-l|佑|to aid}}, {{och-l|祐|''(of divinity)'' to assist; to bless}}, {{och-l|宥|to pardon; magnanimous}} are exoactive derivations of {{och-l|右|id=1}} (ibid.).

